RACE.RACE_TEXT: SANTA ANITA PARK RACE 1 6 1/2F Turf CR: 83. Maiden Special Weight Purse 67000. FOR CALIFORNIA BRED OR CALIFORNIA SIRED MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD. Weight, 122 lbs. (Non-Starters For A Claiming Price Of $40,000 Or Less In Their Last Starts Preferred). (Rail at 20 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: UPWARD MOBILITY raced up close outside the pacesetter, challenged at the three-eighths pole but failed to keep alongside on the turn, chased two wide into the lane, re-bid in upper stretch and took over at the eighth pole, then drew away under right-handed urging. OLD PAL was off slow and steadied behind rival at the start, trailed two wide into the turn, steered out and went four wide into the stretch, angled out wider in the lane and closed well to get up for second. BOTH AT FAULT stalked off the rail, chased two wide into the lane, drifted out in upper stretch, steadied behind COUNTRY BOY who came out in midstretch, finished determinedly late but lost the place. COUNTRY BOY took control early and set the pace up the backstretch, got pressured at the three-eighths pole but quickly moved clear again, challenged again by UPWARD MOBILITY in upper stretch, could not withstand the pressure and relinquished the lead with a furlong left to run, ducked out under left-handed urging midstretch and flattened to fourth. SHIP AND SCAM got crowded between rivals early, bobbled crossing onto the dirt, tracked three deep then outside a rival, spun three wide into the lane, got floated out a bit in upper stretch and could not rally. STAN FROM MALIBU pulled early along the inside off the pace, saved ground to the stretch and lacked a rally. TOPPERS WAGER broke slow, went between rivals then had to steady when boxed in at the nine-sixteenths pole, steadied again into the turn, raced a bit off the rail into the stretch and failed to menace. BUCK OWENS got shuffled back early, rounded the bend three wide and proved no menace.

ENTRY.COMMENT: pulled, inside, no rally

RACE.RACE_TEXT: SANTA ANITA PARK RACE 2 1M Dirt CR: 98. Starter Optional Claiming Purse 40000. FOR FOUR YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $50,000 OR LESS AND WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES OR CLAIMING $50,000 AND WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Weight, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $50,000 (Horses Entered For The Allowance Are Preferred).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: PIROLI stalked the pace from inside, moved out and went between while alongside the leader in the middle stages, took over past the three-eighths pole, cleared late on the far turn and widened under right-handed urging and steady handling late. GOLDENEYE sped to the front and took control of the rail, showed the way inside a pair of rivals to the far turn, was overtaken by PIROLI after crossing the three-eighths pole, stayed alongside then lost touch past the quarter marker and churned on through the lane to best the rest. AMERICAN REFUGEE broke a step slow on the outside, chased three wide early, four deep in the middle stages, continued in the four path on the far turn, grinded out the final furlong and edged CANELO for the show honors. CANELO stumbled leaving the gate, recovered quickly and was forwardly placed two wide, traveled three deep up the backstretch, put in a mild bid outside inner pair on the far turn but could sustain the challenge, chased three to four wide into the lane, weakened in the furlong grounds and got edged for third. CAISSON got crowded leaving the gate, trailed two wide early, traveled along the rail then two wide leaving the far turn and failed to menace.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: CATALINA EDDY set the pace inside a trio of rivals, maintained a short advantage through the turn, shook free at the top of the lane and held safely under urging. MY RANSOM stalked the top quartet from inside into the turn, saved ground through the bend while inching closer, moved off the fence in the drive and finished determinedly for second. MOON ICE forwardly placed four deep up the backstretch, chased three deep into the lane and churned on for a clear third. FINALLY AN EDDIE pressed the pace from between rivals, remained outside the leader through the turn, could not kick on with CATALINA EDDY at the top of the stretch and weakened. THE O G raced outside a rival at the back into the turn, was along the two path through the bend, moved out in the lane and failed to menace. TRANSITORY raced up close three deep and between rivals, got put in a bit tight around the bend, angled into the two path and weakened in the drive. MY DAD IS THIRSTY hit the gate and came away slow, bobbled crossing onto the dirt, trailed while a bit green, traveled inside a rival into the turn, saved ground around the bend and was never a factor.

LUMINIFEROUS bumped with CALIFORNIA BLING before the first turn, tracked inside then steadied at the five-eighths pole, went between runners following the incident, angled four wide on the far turn, came three wide into the stretch, put in a late run but ran out of time.
